---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../config';
---
<Base title="Support · Pillot" description="Get help with Pillot.">
  <article class="container prose">
    <h1>Support</h1>
    <p>Need help with Pillot? We're here.</p>
    <p>Email us at <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a> and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.</p>

    <h2>A label won't scan. What do I do?</h2>
    <p>Try retaking the photo in better light, holding the bottle steady and the label flat. If it still won't read, you can always add the medication by hand. Manual entry gets the same schedule and reminder features as a scanned one.</p>

    <h2>I didn't get a reminder. What happened?</h2>
    <p>Check that Notifications are allowed for Pillot in your iPhone's Settings app, and that Do Not Disturb or Focus modes aren't silencing them. Reminders are sent locally by your phone, so they depend on those permissions being on.</p>

    <h2>How do I delete a medication or clear my data?</h2>
    <p>Since your data lives on your device, you're always in control. Remove individual medications from within the app, or delete Pillot entirely to remove all of its data at once.</p>

    <h2>Does Pillot work without an internet connection?</h2>
    <p>Mostly, yes. Your schedule, reminders, and logging all work offline. Scanning a new label needs a connection, since that's the one moment Pillot reads the photo remotely.</p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  article {
    padding-block: 48px 24px;
  }
</style>
